<p><img src="https://cdn.blot.im/blog_177bc256f0ee469c998e912e20ece048/_image_cache/f64e6e1f-0a36-4bc3-80f0-093f275f6769.jpg" alt="Black line drawing of a person reading a book, knees up, appearing engrossed in the pages. There is a steaming mug of something nearby (probably Tummy Tea), and text that reads “Drink from the pages of a good book”" width="1232" height="1206"></p>
<p><em>Ink on paper, drawn with non-dominant hand. Forgot to erase the pencil lines, whoops!</em></p>
<hr>
<p>A really good book can be just as satisfying as your favourite beverage. The best books are those that leave you changed; wanting to do and be a little better in some aspect of life.</p>
<p>Really drinking from the pages of books like this require deep thinking, not just passive consumption.</p>
